5: Do you know what this place is?
8:
This is where it all began. An altar,
nestled in the depths of a long-lost
city... The place where the dragon
first appeared.
15: A world in which I was never born!
27:
It was here that all those myriad
worlds were conceived... Though it
was merely the byproduct of an
impossible wish.
30:
This was not what Mikoto wanted.
These worlds were not created with
intent, meaning, or purpose.
33:
Everything has been nothing more
than a continuation of that one
simple mistake.
40:
Maybe it was all a mistake. Maybe
that's how the world began. But
none of that matters—I exist, and my
will and thoughts are my own!
43:
And I'm not the only one. Stella, Leve,
and everyone else too... They all
have their own hopes and
dreams—things they believe, people
they care for!
47:
...Even you. You have these things
too, don't you? You're not Hoshi, after
all. 
You're you!
52:
Such strength of will... But not all are
like you, Alk.
55:
Allow me to share with you the
truth—to tell you why it was that
Mikoto Hoshino, the Origin himself,
chose to put an end to everything.
58:
He was weak. A child, in desperate
need of affection which he never
received.
66:
That alone was enough to break his
spirit... It shattered his soul to pieces.
A pathetic sight, wouldn't you say?
71:
But... the same thing happened to
you, didn't it?
78:
Yes... It did! But why? My singular
purpose was to watch over
worlds—to protect and purge them!
82:
Why then did I have to gain a soul?!
Tell me, Alk! Why was this heart
forced upon me, when I never once
asked for it?!
91:
Why? Why must I be a broken shell?!
I begged and pleaded for an
answer...
95:
But it never came! NO ONE could tell
me the truth!
100:
...I'll admit it. I too, am weak. This is
the hideous, pathetic mewling of
someone who can't bear to live any
longer. I want it all to end!
103:
But I can't do it alone. I don't want to
die by myself...
106: That's why I'm taking you all with me.
128:
I could no longer entrust the future
to Stella. Instead, I chose to destroy
it all.
131:
When the Origin Dragon wakes, this
world, and all others, will fade
away—like the fleeting dream they
always were.
134:
No life, no death, no cause and
effect. Neither beginning, nor end. 
No one will be left to wish. To dream.
To hope.
151:
Oh... Yes, that's right... If you put me
down, then I suppose your world
would be saved.
154:
I could accept an end like that.
Because I'm nothing like you, Alk.
185:
The time difference from here to our
world is in the tens of thousands...
Last time, a whole week passed
while we were gone!
191:
All I had to do was buy us some
time...
214:
Okay, crew! Gravity engines to full
thrust! Prepare all six dracocannons!
We're gonna give 'em everything
we've got!
226:
Stars, heed my call...
Open a path before us!
230:
That's so typical of you, Yumu! You
were taking WAY too long to get
back!
234:
Did you SERIOUSLY think I was gonna
sit around and wait for you to get
back?!
